    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - INVERSION VALVE (BENDIX SR-1) - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply parking brakes and block wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain all air reservoirs of air.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark or identify all air lines before disconnecting from inversion valve. Then disconnect
                air lines.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two mounting bolts from valve and remove valve.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
